.TH DHDIREWOLF 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
dhdirewolf \- run Dire Wolf for DigiHub's TNC/digipeater/tracker modes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dhdirewolf
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dhdirewolf
runs
.BR direwolf (1)
against the configuration generated for whichever Direwolf\-backed mode
was last selected with
.BR dhmode (1)
.RI ( tnc ,
.IR tnc300b ,
.IR tracker ,
or
.IR digipeater ).
.PP
.B dhdirewolf
is designed to run under systemd as the
.B dhdirewolf.service
unit, not to be started manually. Unlike
.BR dhgpsmonitor.service
or
.BR dhweb.service ,
it is
.B not
enabled automatically by
.BR install.sh ;
.BR dhmode (1)
enables and starts it the first time one of its modes is selected, and
stops/disables it when switching to any other mode, since Direwolf and
the other digital\-mode services all compete for the same sound card
and cannot run at the same time.
.PP
The configuration file itself is generated by
.B direwolfconf.py
(invoked internally by
.BR dhmode ,
not run directly), which reads
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
(callsign, coordinates, radio interface, rig device) and writes
.IR /etc/digihub/direwolf.conf .
Audio device selection is best\-effort: it looks for a single
plausible non\-built\-in ALSA capture device via
.BR arecord (1)
and falls back to the system default (with a warning in the service
log) if it can't identify one confidently. PTT method is chosen from
the
.B radiointerface
field: CM108\-style USB audio adapters (most inexpensive USB radio
interfaces, including AIOC) use Dire Wolf's automatic
.B PTT CM108
GPIO detection; DigiRig Mobile uses serial RTS on the
.B rigdevice
path; Raspberry Pi audio HATs use
.B PTT GPIO
with the pin number from
.BR rigdevice .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Select a mode (starts/reconfigures this service automatically):
.B dhmode tnc
.TP
Check the running service's status and recent log output:
.B systemctl status dhdirewolf
.br
.B journalctl \-u dhdirewolf \-f
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/digihub/direwolf.conf
Generated configuration; regenerated every time
.BR dhmode (1)
switches to a Direwolf\-backed mode. Do not edit by hand \-\- changes
are overwritten on the next mode switch.
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/dhdirewolf.service
The systemd unit that runs this daemon, installed and enabled by
.BR dhmode (1)
on first use.
.TP
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
Read by
.B direwolfconf.py
to build the configuration.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.B dhdirewolf
does not exit under normal operation; it runs until stopped (e.g. by
systemd).
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded, no mode has been selected
yet
.RI ( /etc/digihub/direwolf.conf
does not exist), or
.B direwolf
is not installed.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR dhmode (1),
.BR dhweb (1),
.BR direwolf (1)
